** MQTT **

# start the data publisher in one terminal

  python3 mqtt_publisher.py

# start the data subscriber in another terminal

  python3 mqtt_subscriber.py

** TCP socket **

# start the TCP server in one terminal

  python3 tcpServer3.py

# start the TCP client in one terminal, then type any string in lower case, which will be sent to the server and bounce back with upper case

  python3 tcpClient3.py

** UDP socket **

# start the UDP server in one terminal

  python3 udpServer3.py

# start the UDP client in one terminal, then type any string in lower case, which will be sent to the server and bounce back with upper case

  python3 udpClient3.py

** TCP command (similar to ssh) **

# start the TCP server in one terminal

  python3 tcpCmdServer3.py

# start the TCP client in one terminal, then type any linux command (such as ls, pwd, etc) and see the results from the remote command server

  python3 tcpClient3.py
